          "text": "Perfect! I have successfully completed the fault localization analysis. Let me create a summary of my findings:\n\n## Fault Localization Summary\n\n**Bug ID**: 207835  \n**Repository**: torvalds/linux  \n**Kernel Version**: 5.6.7  \n**Subsystem**: ACPI Video/Backlight  \n\n### Problem Analysis\n\nThe Acer TravelMate 5735Z laptop experiences a critical backlight control failure:\n- **Default behavior**: Brightness function keys display an OSD in GNOME Shell, but actual brightness doesn't change\n- **With `acpi_backlight=native`**: Brightness control works perfectly (15-16 levels)  \n- **With `acpi_backlight=vendor`**: Acer WMI interface appears but brightness still doesn't work\n- **Writing directly to `/sys/class/backlight/*/brightness`**: Works correctly\n\n### Root Cause\n\nThe bug is in the **ACPI backlight interface selection logic**. The system has two backlight interfaces available:\n1. **ACPI Video Backlight (BACKLIGHT_FIRMWARE)**: Doesn't work on this hardware\n2. **Native Intel Backlight (BACKLIGHT_RAW)**: Works perfectly\n\nThe default selection logic in `acpi_video_get_backlight_type()` returns `acpi_backlight_video` for non-Windows 8 machines. Since the Acer TravelMate 5735Z has a 2011 BIOS (not Windows 8-compatible), it defaults to the non-functional ACPI video backlight.\n\n### Buggy Location\n\n**File**: `drivers/acpi/video_detect.c`  \n**Function/Data Structure**: `video_detect_dmi_table[]` (lines 112-377)\n\n**Issue**: Missing a DMI quirk entry for the Acer TravelMate 5735Z that would force it to use native backlight mode instead of the default ACPI video backlight.\n\n### The Fix\n\nA DMI entry needs to be added to the `video_detect_dmi_table[]` array that matches:\n- `DMI_SYS_VENDOR`: \"Acer\"\n- `DMI_PRODUCT_NAME`: \"TravelMate 5735Z\"  \n- `DMI_BOARD_NAME`: \"BA51_MV\"\n\nAnd calls `video_detect_force_native()` to force `acpi_backlight_native`, similar to existing entries like the Lenovo IdeaPad S405 quirk.\n\nThe result has been written to `/workspace/fault_localization_result.json` with confidence level 0.95.",
