        {
          "arguments": {
            "content": "{\n  \"buggy_files\": [\n    \"drivers/acpi/video_detect.c\"\n  ],\n  \"buggy_functions\": [\n    \"video_detect_dmi_table\"\n  ],\n  \"confidence\": 0.95,\n  \"reasoning\": \"The Acer TravelMate 5735Z laptop fails to properly control backlight brightness via ACPI video interface on Linux 5.6.7. The root cause is a missing DMI quirk entry in the video_detect_dmi_table array. The system lacks a DMI-based quirk to force native backlight mode for this specific Acer model. Without this quirk, the default backlight selection logic returns acpi_backlight_video (suitable for newer Windows 8-compatible machines), but the Acer TravelMate 5735Z's ACPI video backlight implementation doesn't work correctly. When users manually specify acpi_backlight=native via kernel parameters, the native Intel backlight (BACKLIGHT_RAW type) works perfectly with 15-16 brightness levels. The fix requires adding a DMI entry matching sys_vendor='Acer', product_name='TravelMate 5735Z', and board_name='BA51_MV' to call video_detect_force_native() in the video_detect_dmi_table[], similar to existing entries for other problematic Acer and laptop models (such as Lenovo IdeaPad S405 at line 290).\"\n}\n",
            "file_path": "/workspace/fault_localization_result.json"
          },
          "step_id": 52,
          "timestamp": "2026-03-02T22:19:23.766Z",
          "tool": "Write"
