        {
          "arguments": {
            "command": "cat > /tmp/verification.txt << 'EOF'\nBUG REPORT DMI DATA:\n- sys_vendor: Acer\n- product_name: TravelMate 5735Z\n- board_name: BA51_MV\n- product_version: V1.14\n- bios_version: V1.14\n- bios_date: 07/26/2011 (old BIOS, not Windows 8 compatible)\n\nKEY SYMPTOMS:\n1. Default backlight: OSD shows but brightness doesn't change\n2. With acpi_backlight=native: Works perfectly (15-16 levels)\n3. With acpi_backlight=vendor: acer-wmi appears but brightness doesn't work\n4. Writing directly to /sys/class/backlight/*/brightness works\n\nROOT CAUSE:\n- The backlight selection logic in video_detect.c line 413-450\n- For non-Windows 8 machines, default is acpi_backlight_video (line 449)\n- But the Acer TravelMate 5735Z's ACPI video backlight doesn't work correctly\n- The native Intel backlight (BACKLIGHT_RAW) works fine\n- Missing DMI quirk to force native backlight for this model\n\nFIX LOCATION:\nFile: drivers/acpi/video_detect.c\nArray: video_detect_dmi_table[] (lines 112-377)\nMissing: DMI entry to call video_detect_force_native() for Acer TravelMate 5735Z\nSimilar to existing entries like Lenovo Ideapad S405 (line 290)\n\nBACKLIGHT TYPE CLASSIFICATION:\n- BACKLIGHT_FIRMWARE: ACPI video (default, doesn't work for Acer)\n- BACKLIGHT_RAW: Intel native (works for Acer)\nEOF\ncat /tmp/verification.txt\n"
